#: ../../introducing.rst:1080
msgid ""
"Click the word :guilabel:`Empty`, which represents the DVD reader. To access"
" the |trueos| installer from the DVD reader, double-check the "
":guilabel:`Slot` is pointing to the correct location (e.g. :guilabel:`IDE "
"Secondary Master`) and use the drop-down menu to change the location if "
"incorrect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introducing.rst:1086
msgid ""
"If using an ISO stored on the hard disk is preferred, click the "
":guilabel:`DVD` icon then :guilabel:`Choose a virtual CD/DVD disk file` to "
"open a browser menu to navigate to the location of the ISO. Highlight the "
"desired ISO and click :guilabel:`Open`. The name of the ISO will now appear "
"in the :guilabel:`Storage Tree` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introducing.rst:1092
msgid ""
"|trueos| is now ready to be installed into the virtual machine as a guest "
"OS. Highlight the virtual machine and click on the green :guilabel:`Start` "
"icon. A new window opens, indicating the virtual machine is starting. If a "
"DVD is inserted, it should audibly spin and the machine will start to boot "
"into the installation program. If it does not or if using an ISO stored on "
"the hard disk, press :kbd:`F12` to select the boot device when the message "
"to do so appears, then press :kbd:`c` to boot from CD-ROM. Proceed through "
"the installation as described in the :ref:`Install` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introducing.rst:1102
msgid ""
"If the installer GUI doesn't appear to load after configuring the virtual "
"machine, **EFI** may need to be enabled in Virtualbox by navigating "
":menuselection:`Settings --> System --> Motherboard` and checking "
":guilabel:`Enable EFI (special OSes only)`."
